    bibo:endPage "716" ;
    bibo:journal "Vertebrate Zoology" ;
    bibo:pubDate "2023-09-19" ;
    bibo:startPage "697" ;
    bibo:volume "73" ;
    dc:creator "Idiiatullina, Sabira S.; Pawangkhanant, Parinya; Tawan, Tanapong; Worranuch, Thanawut; Dechochai, Bunyarit; Suwannapoom, Chatmongkon; Nguyen, Tan Van; Chanhome, Lawan; Poyarkov, Nikolay A." ;
    dc:date "2023" ;
    dc:title "Limestone jewel: A new colourful karst-dwelling pitviper (Serpentes: Viperidae: Trimeresurus) from the poorly explored borderlands of southern peninsular Thailand" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.3897/vz.73.e109854.figure3>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.3897/vz.73.e109854.figure4>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.3897/vz.73.e109854.figure5>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.3897/vz.73.e109854.figure6>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.3897/vz.73.e109854.figure7>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.3897/vz.73.e109854.figure1> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.3897/vz.73.e109854.figure3>
    dc:description "Figure 3. The holotype of Trimeresurus ciliaris sp. nov. in life (ZMMU Re- 17661, adult male) from Thum Khao Ting, Palian District, Trang Province, Thailand. A dorsolateral and B ventral view of body; C head in dorsal, D in ventral, E in lateral right, and F in lateral left aspects; G right hemipenis, partially everted; H close-up of dorsal scales. Photographs by P. Pawangkhanant." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/908085" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.3897/vz.73.e109854.figure4>
    dc:description "Figure 4. Variation in head scalation and coloration in male paratypes of Trimeresurus ciliaris sp. nov.: A ZMMU Re- 17661; B ZMMU Re- 17662; C AUP- 02011; and D ZMMU Re- 17663. See Table 4 for details. Photographs by P. Pawangkhanant." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/908086" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.3897/vz.73.e109854.figure5>
    dc:description "Figure 5. Comparison of body coloration between males of A Trimeresurus ciliaris sp. nov.; B T. kanburiensis; C T. kuiburi; and D T. venustus s. str. Photographs by P. Pawangkhanant (A, B, D) and T. Woranuch (C)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/908087" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.3897/vz.73.e109854.figure6>
    dc:description "Figure 6. Comparison of head coloration (left profile and dorsal view of the head) between males of A-B Trimeresurus ciliaris sp. nov.; C - D T. kanburiensis; E - F T. kuiburi; and G - H T. venustus s. str. Photographs by P. Pawangkhanant (A-D), A. Kaosung (E-F, H) and M. Naiduangchan (G)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/908088" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.3897/vz.73.e109854.figure7>
    dc:description "Figure 7. Habitat of Trimeresurus ciliaris sp. nov. A microhabitat of the new species near the Thum Khao Ting Cave, Palian District, Trang Province, Thailand; B holotype ZMMU Re- 17661, adult male, in life in situ; C paratype QSMI 1538, adult female, in life in situ; D - E male specimen from Wang Kelian, Perlis State, Malaysia (not collected). Photographs by P. Pawangkhanant (A-C) and Azrul Azrizal Azmy (D-E)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/908089" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.3897/vz.73.e109854.figure1>
    dc:description "Figure 1. Distribution of the Trimeresurus kanburiensis species complex in Thai-Malay Peninsula: Localities. T. kanburiensis (yellow): 1 Kanchanaburi Prov., Sai Yok Dist., Wat Tham, Phom Lo Khao Yai; T. kuiburi (blue): 2 Prachuap Khiri Khan Prov., Kuiburi Dist., Wat Khao Daeng; 3 Prachuap Khiri Khan Prov., Kuiburi Dist., Khao Daeng Beach; 4 Prachuap Khiri Khan Prov., Kuiburi Dist., Khao Daeng, near Ban Thung Noi; T. cf. venustus (1) (green): 5 Chumphon Prov., Wat Tham Sanook; T. venustus s. str. (pink): 6 Krabi Prov., Mueang Krabi Dist., Tiger Cave viewpoint; 7 Thailand, Nakhon Si Thammarat Prov., Khao Luang; 8 Nakhon Si Thammarat Prov., Thung Song; 9 Surat Thani Prov.; Trimeresurus ciliaris sp. nov. (red): 10 Trang Prov., Palian Dist., Thum Khao Ting; 11 Tha Le Ban NP., Khuan Don Dist., Satun Prov.; 12 Perlis State National Park, Perlis State; T. cf. venustus (2) (purple): 13 Pulau Langkawi Island, Kedah State. Remark: stars denote type localities (the type locality is not shown for T. kanburiensis as it was not sampled). Abbreviations: MY - Myanmar, MA - Malaysia, Prov. - Province, Dist. - District." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/908083" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

